{#def target, inline=False, extra="" #}
{#
  Field label for form inputs. ``target`` is the id of the input
  this label is for (renders as the HTML ``for`` attribute -- the
  prop can't be called ``for`` because JinjaX parses the prop
  declaration block as a Python function signature, and ``for`` is
  a reserved keyword).

  Two layouts:

  ``inline=False`` (default) -- a block label that sits above the
  input, with ``mb-6`` bottom spacing. Used by the auth flow stack
  (email / password) and the Create form's vertical form sections.

  ``inline=True`` -- an inline label that sits in a horizontal flex
  row beside its input (typically next to a Select). No display /
  margin classes are added; the parent flex row handles layout.

  Usage: a FormLabel with target="email" renders as a block label
  above an input; adding ``inline`` flips it to a horizontal-row
  treatment for cases like a label sitting beside a Select.
#}
{%- set _layout = "" if inline else "block mb-6" -%}
<label for="{{ target }}" class="text-sm font-medium text-primary {{ _layout }} {{ extra }}">{{ content }}</label>
